Description: Painted wooden shabti of Aset, Chantress of Amun and Lady of The House with a black lappet-wig, a yellow face with black traced eyes and a red and blue collar; the hands are unmarked; the front of the leg section is inscribed with a column of black painted Hieroglyphs.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Somerset Lowry-Corry, 2nd Earl of Belmore (perhaps)
